# Backend Module - Code Generation
#
# Unified code generation backend supporting multiple target architectures
# and compilation strategies. Provides automatic backend selection based on
# target platform, optimization level, and build mode.
#
# Supported Backends:
#   - Cranelift: Default JIT/AOT backend (fast compilation)
#   - LLVM: Advanced optimizations, wider platform support
#   - Native: Direct machine code generation (x86_64, ARM64, RISC-V)
#   - WASM: WebAssembly for browser/embedding
#   - CUDA: GPU compute via CUDA/PTX
#   - Vulkan: GPU compute via SPIR-V
#   - Interpreter: Direct HIR/MIR interpretation
#   - Lean: Formal verification export
#
# Public API:
#   - use compiler_core.backend.backend_api.{Backend}
#   - use compiler_core.backend.backend_types.{BackendKind, CodegenTarget}
#   - use compiler_core.backend.backend_factory.{create_backend}
#
# Architecture:
#   - backend_api.spl: Unified backend interface
#   - backend_types.spl: Type definitions
#   - backend_factory.spl: Backend instantiation
#   - backend_selector.spl: Automatic selection logic
#   - *_backend.spl: Individual backend implementations
#
# Sub-modules:
#   - common/: Shared backend utilities
#   - native/: Direct machine code generation
#   - cuda/: CUDA/PTX code generation
#   - vulkan/: SPIR-V generation

# All submodules are automatically available through the module system.
# The backend is typically accessed through the driver or compilation context.
